claim.claim-text:
10. A comfort strip for controlling under pant garments from becoming wedged within the declivity formed by the buttocks having: 
a top portion, the top portion adapted to conform to a body region; 
a bottom portion, the bottom portion adapted to couple to an under pant garment; 
a pair of opposing side portions; and 
a pair of flaps, one extending respectively from opposite side portions whereby the pair of flaps are adapted to couple to an under pant garment.

14. At least one horizontally placed comfort strip for controlling under pant garments from becoming wedged within the declivity formed by the buttocks having: 
a top portion; 
a bottom portion, the bottom portion adapted to couple to a rear portion of an under pant garment; 
a pair of opposing side portions; whereby 
the top portion, bottom portion, and opposing side is a semi-rigid material that has a memory and retains it shape.
